The paper focuses on multi-task robotic skill learning, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method involves learning from play data using unsupervised learning techniques, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method also involves organizing the play data in an embedding space, which is related to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the method is designed to handle variability in the play data, which is related to control systems (cs.SY).
